5:
...And you say that this
princess-priestess of the birdfolk
wishes to meet with us?
8:
Indeed she does. Once I told her
about the journeys we've had, she
insisted.
12:
Priestesses are pretty important
among birdfolk, right? AND she's a
princess? Gosh, I'm starting to get
cold feet...
15:
Heh-heh, no need to get anxious.
She's actually pretty fun to be
around.
21:
Oh, Aurore... You could at least show
some amount of respect—
35:
L-Lady Zephyr?! What are you doing
here?
39:
Forgive me, Cran. I simply could not
wait!
43:
And you! That adorable
appearance... You must be the
champion that King Whitetail spoke
of!
47:
Oh, yes! I have so much to ask you.
Is it true that there are people made
entirely of metal on other worlds?!
People who can fly without the use
of wings?!
51:
I... W-well, you see... Perhaps it's wise
to calm down first—
56:
*gasp* Upon closer inspection... 
I was right! You're flying without
wings!
60:
Amazing! Incredible! You truly ARE 
a champion from another world!
64: What'd I tell you? She's pretty fun, eh?
72:
...So you travel to all sorts of different
worlds? That sounds positively
splendid!
75:
You seem very interested in other
worlds, Zephyr.
78:
I am! Oh, and in all of you, of course!
Ever since Aurore and Cran spoke to
me about your adventures, I have
been dying to—
81:
Those wings... Might you be the
priestess-princess of the birdfolk?
83:
If it's not too much trouble, could
you give this child a blessing?
84:
See, I took them in after their
parents died in the war, 
and... Well, I just want them to have 
a good future.
91:
I shall do what I can.
Come now, dear.
95:
Hm... This princess of the birdfolk
seems quite famous.
99:
It's said that those born with
different-colored wings are blessed,
destined to be servants to a higher
power. To birdfolk, she's special.
103:
Special? I don't think so. Without this
spear, I would be entirely flightless.
107:
That reminds me, how did you get
permission from the Chief to leave? 
I would've expected him to refuse.
112: Oh, that? W-well, you see... Uhm...
116:
M-My Lady! Thank goodness you're
safe! Why would you go off on your
own like that?!
119: So much for getting permission, huh?
130:
I apologize! Th-there's a reason I left
without a word, you see! I... uhm...
133:
Don't worry. You can tell us. We're on
your side.
137:
...I thought I would not be allowed to
leave. In fact, I have never been
allowed to leave the village before...
142:
Understandable, considering your
unique role... But that must be very
inconvenient.
146:
No, not at all! In fact, I find myself to
be quite blessed.
149:
A flightless bird like me was not only
made a priestess, but was given the
means to fly. In this world, I am one
of the fortunate ones.
153:
And... you're sure about that? 
I thought you wanted to leave 
your village.
156:
Well, yes... Hearing about the outside
world, I found it all so very exciting...
159:
...But, you see... More than that, there
has been this nagging feeling, an
uncertainty deep within me. 
And I do not know why...
162:
That is why I wish to leave—to soar
the skies of other worlds. To feel their
winds with my own feathers, and
know.
172:
Ahh! Right, they must still be looking
for me! I should probably return as
soon as possible...
177:
What if you told them, Zephyr? 
You shouldn't be ashamed of 
how you feel.
187:
Forgive me for leaving
unannounced. I should have
consulted you first.
190:
I... I want to go to other worlds. I want
to see them with my own eyes!
194:
Please! I will convince the Chief
myself, so if you could just—
198:
We understand. When it comes time
to convince the Chief, we'll back you
up, my lady.
205:
I mean, we've known for a while now.
Your eyes would light up the
moment we spoke of the outside
world. Don't tell me you were trying
to hide it?
209: Wh-what?! Was it truly so obvious?
212:
Don't worry, my lady. 
Whatever it is you wish to do, 
we will be there to support you.
214:
That being said, you should be
prepared for the scolding of a
lifetime. The Chief was quite upset,
you know. He was crying for at least
an hour.
217: Ohh... I hate seeing the Chief cry...
221:
Looks like lady luck has smiled upon
you, Zephyr.
226:
Indeed she has! 
Thank you... All of you!
234:
This is amazing! So this is Starview
Village! And those... Those are
worlds! Stars!
238:
I'm glad we were there to help out.
I'm sure it would've been hard to
convince the Chief by herself.
241:
Took at least an hour to stop the
Chief from crying, but we did. And it
was worth it—just look at that smile
on her face!
250:
Thank you, thank you! I am very
much excited to go on adventures
with you!
